From: 3090 team <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: 2026-05-26
Subject: [PATCH] gemma4_causal: num_experts getattr fallback for dense Gemma4

Dense Gemma4 variants (gemma4-31b = gemma-4-31B-it-AutoRound-AWQ) load via
gemma4_causal.py and have NO MoE experts — their config omits `num_experts`
entirely. `load_weights` unconditionally read `self.config.num_experts`, so
the dense 31B crashed at load on v0.5.12:

    File "python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_causal.py", line 1037, in load_weights
        num_experts = self.config.num_experts
    AttributeError: 'Gemma4Config' object has no attribute 'num_experts'

The value is only consumed inside the expert-weight loop, which never matches
for a dense checkpoint (no `experts.gate_up_proj` / `experts.down_proj`
weights), so 0 is safe. Mirrors the guard already present in gemma4_mm.py:779
(`getattr(self.config.text_config, "num_experts", 0) or 0`). The 26B MoE
(gemma4) is unaffected — it ships num_experts.

Verified 2026-05-26: gemma4-31b boots TP=2 and validates basic + tool_call +
thinking + vision after this fallback; gemma4 (26B MoE) still 5/5.

diff --git a/python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_causal.py b/python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_causal.py
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_causal.py
+++ b/python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_causal.py
@@ -1034,7 +1034,12 @@ class Gemma4ForCausalLM(nn.Module):
             ("experts.w13_weight", "experts.gate_up_proj", ("w1", "w3")),
             ("experts.w2_weight", "experts.down_proj", ("w2",)),
         ]
-        num_experts = self.config.num_experts
+        # Dense Gemma4 variants (e.g. gemma4-31b) have no MoE experts and omit
+        # `num_experts` from their config entirely. The expert loop below never
+        # matches for dense checkpoints (no experts.* weights), so 0 is safe;
+        # the bare attribute access would otherwise AttributeError at load.
+        # Mirrors the getattr guard already in gemma4_mm.py.
+        num_experts = getattr(self.config, "num_experts", 0) or 0

         k_eq_v_layers = self._get_k_eq_v_layers()

